                    <sp:description>Light can enter the telescope section through either a 40mm x 40mm entrance aperture (i.e. the airglow channel) or a stopped-down 1-mm diameter entrance aperture and flat relay mirror (i.e. the solar occultation channel) and is collected and focused by an off-axisparaboloidal (OAP) primary mirror onto the spectrograph entrance slit.</sp:description>
