                </sp:Field_of_View>
                <sp:Bin_Description>
					<sp:bin_profile_description>The active area starts at spectral pixel 130 and ends at pixel 910, which corresponds to a total wavelength passband between 465 and 1881 Angstrom. 
                    The lookup file referenced below contains a 1D array of wavelengths (in Angstrom) associated with each of the 1024 pixel indices along the spectral axis in the data file. The provided bin width is an approximation. 
                    The actual spectral PSF varies as a nonlinear function of wavelength and aperture, but FWHM values are generally between ~3 and ~4 Angstrom.
                    </sp:bin_profile_description>
